<item>
            <title>[CSI-7162] Implement Push Notification to Jira on Opportunity Change</title>
                <link>https://onezelis.atlassian.net/browse/CSI-7162</link>
                <project id="11041" key="CSI">Salesforce Implementation - OneZelis</project>
                    <description>&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;UserStory&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;User Story&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;As a&lt;/b&gt; Salesforce / Jira Integration Administrator&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;I want&lt;/b&gt; Salesforce to publish a Platform Event when qualifying Opportunity changes occur and process that event via an Apex Platform Event trigger that invokes the Jira Connector&lt;br/&gt;
So that Jira can automatically pull the latest Opportunity data and remain synchronized with Salesforce without manual intervention&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;BusinessValue&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Business Value&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ensures near&#8209;real&#8209;time synchronization between Salesforce Opportunities and Jira issues&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Eliminates manual sync actions and reduces data inconsistency risks&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Provides a scalable, asynchronous, and supportable integration pattern&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Improves auditability and troubleshooting of cross&#8209;system updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;InScope&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;In Scope&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Opportunity create/update events in Salesforce&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Salesforce Platform Event publication&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Apex Platform Event trigger implementation&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Invocation of the existing Jira Connector Apex class&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Logging and traceability of sync requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;OutofScope&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Out of Scope&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bidirectional sync logic initiated from Jira&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Non&#8209;Opportunity Salesforce objects&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Field&#8209;level data mapping changes inside the Jira Connector&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jira&#8209;side configuration changes beyond receiving pull notifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;AcceptanceCriteria&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Acceptance Criteria&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When a qualifying Opportunity is created or updated in Salesforce, a Platform Event is published.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Only defined Opportunity changes (mapped fields, status changes, or business&#8209;critical attributes) trigger event publication.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Opportunity save transactions are not blocked or delayed by Jira availability or connector performance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A Salesforce Apex trigger subscribes to the Platform Event and executes asynchronously.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Platform Event trigger invokes the Jira Connector Apex class to notify Jira of the Opportunity update.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jira successfully receives the notification and initiates an automatic pull of the updated Opportunity data.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Duplicate or recursive sync scenarios are prevented.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Each sync request can be traced to its originating Opportunity and Salesforce transaction.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Errors during event processing or Jira notification are logged and discoverable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The solution is deployable and testable in Salesforce sandbox and Jira non&#8209;production environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;TechnicalSolutionDescription&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Technical Solution Description&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;IntegrationPattern&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Integration Pattern&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Opportunity Trigger &#8594; Platform Event &#8594; Platform Event Trigger &#8594; Jira Connector&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This design decouples Salesforce data changes from external system calls, ensuring resilience, scalability, and observability.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;SalesforceComponents&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Salesforce Components&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;1.OpportunityTrigger&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. Opportunity Trigger&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Detects qualifying Opportunity create/update events&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Evaluates defined trigger conditions&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Publishes a lightweight Platform Event&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Contains no direct Jira connector logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;2.PlatformEvent&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;2. Platform Event&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Event Name: Opportunity_Sync_Request__e&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Purpose: Signal that an Opportunity has changed and Jira should pull updated data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Event Payload Fields:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Opportunity_Id__c (Text, 18)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Change_Type__c (Text &#8211; Create / Update)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Event_Timestamp__c (DateTime)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Transaction_Id__c (Text, used for traceability and correlation)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Source_System__c (Text &#8211; Salesforce)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;3.PlatformEventApexTrigger&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;3. Platform Event Apex Trigger&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Subscribes to Opportunity_Sync_Request__e (after insert)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Runs asynchronously by design&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Invokes the Jira Connector Apex class entry point&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sends notification only; does not pass full Opportunity payload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;JiraIntegration&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Jira Integration&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Follows Appfire&#8217;s &#8220;Push from Salesforce &#8594; Pull from Jira&#8221; model&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Salesforce sends a notification indicating a change occurred&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jira Connector performs the authoritative pull of Opportunity data&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Salesforce remains the system of record&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Logging%2CMonitoring%2CandAudit&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Logging, Monitoring, and Audit&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Each Platform Event includes identifiers to trace:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Opportunity&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Salesforce transaction&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sync request timing&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Errors during event handling or connector invocation are logged&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Logs are visible via Salesforce debug logs and/or a custom sync logging object&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sync history can be reported on for operational visibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;ErrorHandling&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Error Handling&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Platform Event publication failures do not block Opportunity saves&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Connector invocation failures are logged for investigation&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jira retry behavior is handled on the Jira side per connector configuration&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;No automatic recursive retries from Salesforce triggers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Non%E2%80%91FunctionalRequirements&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Non&#8209;Functional Requirements&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Solution must remain within Salesforce governor limits under expected Opportunity update volumes&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Events must be asynchronous and non&#8209;blocking&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Platform Event usage must align with Salesforce event limits&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Integration must be resilient to temporary Jira outages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;DefinitionofReady&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Definition of Ready&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;This story is considered ready when:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Triggering Opportunity fields and events are finalized&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Platform Event schema is approved&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jira Connector entry point is identified&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sandbox and non&#8209;prod Jira access are available&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Logging and error&#8209;handling expectations are agreed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;DefinitionofDone&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;b&gt;Definition of Done&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;This story is complete when:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Platform Event is created and deployed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Opportunity trigger publishes events correctly&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Platform Event trigger calls Jira Connector successfully&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Jira pulls updated Opportunity data as expected&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Errors are logged and traceable&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Solution is validated in sandbox and non&#8209;prod Jira&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Documentation is updated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;hr /&gt;

